  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0db1\u0ddc\u0db8\u0daf \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "They are supporting Sri Lanka to get out of the crisis",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Chi Shenhong, the Chinese Ambassador, said in Kandy that the Chinese government will continue to support Sri Lanka in order to rescue Sri Lanka from the temporary economic crisis it is currently facing.",
        "He came to Kandy yesterday (27) and visited the Malwatu Asgiri elders and emphasized that in the media and further said:",
        "\"Although the current economic crisis in Sri Lanka will not end overnight, it is the belief of the Chinese government that Sri Lanka has the ability to get out of it within a short and reasonable period of time. In addition to the Chinese government's cooperation aid grant, the Chinese Buddhist Association has planned a program to provide aid for the revival of temples and Buddhism in this country.",
        "Although there have been various changes in Sri Lanka recently, there has been no change in the Sri Lanka-China friendship. The aim of the Chinese government is to maintain bilateral relations between the two countries. We believe that Sri Lanka has the ability to get out of the difficult situation. The Chinese government also supports it.\""
      ],
